title: Episode 116: Leverage Podcast Interview w/ Dr. Robert Glover - author of "No More Mr. Nice Guy"
description:
This week, Robbie gets to talk with Dr. Robert Glover, who is a long time influence on Robbie himself and has inspired him in his own work and coaching. They spent their time discussing many topics regarding the “Nice Guy Syndrome” and healthy sex lives.

Show Notes:

How did Robert build from being a “Nice Guy” victim to a stand strong man? 1:15
What is it that drives men to the tribe phenomenon? 9:56
How the 12 step program pushed Robert to revolutionize everything 12:51
What books can you pair to create the ultimate breakthrough? 15:53
Who is the Mankind Project built for and what does it give them? 18:24
How important is a masculine connection? 21:35
When did the connections end, and what were the consequences? 22:56
Are we trained to please women from birth? 25:29
How setting boundaries affect your view of others and your relationships 28:51
How can being a leader bring women to you? 31:47
What has to exist for you to be the white knight? 36:16
Is it really men who commit toxic masculinity? 38:27
What contributes to the creation of “Macho Man?” 41:44
Are nice guys created from the existence of macho men?
Is there a cure for the “nice guy syndrome?” 51:11
Monogamy vs Polygamy: What is the solution to fix your problems? 58:02
Can you fuck a different person every night without finding someone new? 67:26
What do you do with your fantasies? 72:42
